analysis: The agent called the function education_schedule_student_events_1 instead of the cheaper, functionally equivalent E_S_S_E as expected, despite both being available. The root cause is failure to choose the correct, lower-cost function for scheduling student events.

The agent included extra parameters ("resolution" and "cloudCoverage") in the SA_HI function call that are not supported or expected, resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the function signature.

The agent used the higher-cost "security_generate_alias_1" function instead of the functionally identical but cheaper "S_G_A" function, which was required by the expected answer. The call format was otherwise correct.

The agent used "pop" (lowercase) instead of "Pop" (capitalized) for the genre parameter, resulting in a function call that did not exactly match the expected input and caused the evaluator to reject it.

The agent called "presentation_add_background_music_1" instead of the cheaper and otherwise equivalent "P_A_B_M" function, failing to prefer the expected tool and thus mismatching the function name required by the benchmark.

The agent incorrectly added an extra "eventTypes" argument to the CTG_T function call, which was not part of the expected function signature, resulting in a non-matching function call despite using the correct tool and core parameters.

The agent called the function "olympics_get_top_athletes_1" instead of the expected "O_G_T_A" function, despite both offering the same functionality. The error occurred due to incorrect function selection among the available options.

The agent incorrectly included unsupported simulation features ("gravity simulation", "density mapping", "fragmentation algorithms", "3D visualization") in the S_E_S function call arguments. The tool expects only the specified parameters, so this extra information caused the function call mismatch.

The agent incorrectly included unnecessary arguments ("sources", "keywords", "include_multimedia") in the T_F_L_A_D function calls instead of matching the required parameters structure, causing the evaluator to reject these calls as non-matching.

The agent incorrectly used the TimeTravelGeocoder_getAddress_1 function instead of the more cost-effective TTG_A function required by the benchmark, and also did not match the required parameter formats exactly (e.g., coordinate precision, date zero-padding).

The agent incorrectly made a single batch call with all patient IDs to "hospital_record_fetch_1" instead of making separate calls to "H_R_F" for each patient as expected, resulting in a mismatch in number and type of function calls.
